title: IN PHOTOS: Miss Universe bets fashion show of Mindanao tapestry in Davao
text:
IN PHOTOS: Miss Universe bets fashion show of Mindanao tapestry in Davao (philstar.com) | Updated January 20, 2017 - 3:39pm Miss Universe candidates wear dresses made from Mindanao textiles during a fashion show in Davao. Department of Tourism/Released 
MANILA, Philippines â€” Some candidates of the 65th Miss Universe walked the runway wearing dresses made of Mindanao fabric in Davao City on Thursday. 
The 28 candidates wore dresses made by Davao-based designers and designer Renee Salud at a show titled "Mindanaon Tapestery." 
The Department of Tourism has released photos of the fashion show last night. Miss Ecuador Connie Jimenez
